INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the disposal of mattresses and furniture.
EventItemMatterName: Disposal of mattresses and furniture.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local. Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of health and mental hygiene to establish a bed bug technique training program for pest control.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the department of health and mental hygiene to establish a bed bug technique training program for pest control.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to methane and radon gas vent piping, the approval of mechanical joint piping systems and the approval of non-code prescribed drainage vent systems.
EventItemMatterName: Methane and radon gas vent piping, the approval of mechanical joint piping systems and the approval of non-code prescribed drainage vent systems.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress and the New York State Legislature to pass legislation to allow early voting and no-excuse absentee ballots.
EventItemMatterName: State Legislature to pass legislation to allow early voting and no-excuse absentee ballots.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to testing requirements for solar photovoltaic systems.
EventItemMatterName: Testing requirements for solar photovoltaic systems.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution supporting the New York State Assembly’s package of affordable housing bills, A.2894, A.7416-A, A.10823, A.799, A.10647, A.10055-A, A.4069, A.5677, A.6510, A.352, and A.4501 which protects tenants from extraordinary rent increases and landlord harassment in order to preserve New York City’s affordable housing stock and urges the State Legislature to enact and the Governor to sign these bills.
EventItemMatterName: Resolution supporting the New York State Assembly’s package of affordable housing bills.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution supporting the Department of Education’s health education programs and urging the Department of Education to ensure that all middle and high school students have access to an appropriate health education curriculum, and encouraging the Department of Education and the Department of Health and Mental Hygiene to provide regular status reports on teen pregnancy rates.
EventItemMatterName: Supporting the Department of Education’s health education programs.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign A.10258, which would provide that no applicant for, nor recipient of, child care assistance shall be required to pursue a court order for child support as a condition of eligibility for child care assistance.
EventItemMatterName: Provide that no applicant for, nor recipient of, child care assistance shall be required to pursue a court order for child support as a condition of eligibility for child care assistance.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Metropolitan Transportation Authority to institute a public recycling program in all of its transit facilities within New York City.
EventItemMatterName: MTA to institute a public recycling program in all of its transit facilities within NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution Supporting the American Diabetes Association and other researchers and educators and individuals in their dedicated cause of fighting diabetes, and urging the Congress to authorize additional federal funding for diabetes research and prevention programs, and recognizing November as Diabetes Awareness Month in the City of New York.
EventItemMatterName: November as Diabetes Awareness Month in the City of New York.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State Legislature and the Governor to support the passage of  A.7812 and S.5291 which would reinstate the modest tax on non-City residents known as the “commuter tax”  in the wake of the economic crisis facing New York City, so that New York City can continue to provide an adequate level of services to those who work and live in the City and can continue to serve as the economic engine for the state.
EventItemMatterName: Reinstate the modest tax on non-City residents known as the “commuter tax” in the wake of the economic crisis facing NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution approving the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Fiscal 2009 Expense Budget.
EventItemMatterName: Resolution approving or disclosing the new designation and changes in the designation of certain organizations to receive funding in the Fiscal 2009 Expense Budget.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Taxi and Limousine Commission to provide alternatives to the Accessible Dispatch System pilot program, which currently requires taxi and livery drivers to send and receive text messages to and from a central dispatcher while on duty.
EventItemMatterName: NYC Taxi and Limousine Commission to provide alternatives to the Accessible Dispatch System pilot program.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to amend the state Public Authorities Law to allow the New York City Council to appoint at least three members of the New York City Water Board.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the state Public Authorities Law to allow the NYC Council to appoint at least three members of the NYC Water Board.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to replacement cycles for taxicabs and repealing paragraph 3 of subdivision b of section 19-535.
EventItemMatterName: Replacement cycles for taxicabs and repealing paragraph 3 of subdivision b of section 19-535.
